items.title: Boy suffers 'serious' leg injuries after shark bite at Sydney Harbour beach
items.standfirst: A boy has been pulled from a Sydney Harbour beach after being bitten by a shark, police say.
items.content: A boy has been pulled from a Sydney Harbour beach after being bitten by a shark, police say.The boy, believed to be about 12, was being treated for "serious" leg injuries.Emergency services were called to Hermitage Foreshore Walk on Steele Point Road at Vaucluse, near Shark Beach, about 4.20pm.Intensive care paramedics and the Care Flight helicopter were sent to the scene, a NSW Ambulance spokeswoman told 9news.com.au.Images show multiple ambulances and police by Rose Bay Wharf.The beach has been closed and swimmers are advised to avoid the water, police said.

clusters.neutral_headline: Man, 41, charged over Canberra pipe bombs

items.title: Man, 41, charged over Canberra pipe bombs
items.standfirst: Police found the devices - which they say they don't think are terror related - on streets in Belconnen.
items.content: A 41-year-old man has been arrested after multiple pipe bombs were found in Canberra.Police found the devices - which they say they don't think are terror related - on streets in Belconnen.The 15 devices were found around Lake Ginninderra between Joynton Smith Drive and Ginninderra Drive.READ MORE: Landslide almost takes out Sydney home as flash floods and storms batter NSW Police allege the man bought and stole items used to create the pipe bombs from a Bunnings.Residents in the area were told to stay away as police retrieved all of the bombs, some of which had already exploded.Police say they have searched the area and are confident they've found them all.It's alleged officers found items used to make the bombs after searching the man's home.READ MORE: Fears grow as Indonesian plane with 11 people onboard vanishes READ MORE: Iran's leader admits thousands dead after protests, but calls Trump a 'criminal' The 41-year-old was arrested at a unit in Gungahlin.He has been charged with unauthorised manufacture of a prohibited dangerous substance, possessing a prohibited weapon and theft.He will face the ACT Magistrates Court on Monday.
